////Capsule

Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And	I'm on Page 07 - Joint & Bursae of Shoulder MRI
When I select the radio button 'Finding'
Then 'Finding' dropdown menu is enabled

When I select 'Capsule' from the Finding dropdown
Then 'Add new finding' button is enabled
And 'Osteochondromatosis' radio button is enabled
And 'Adhesive Capsulitis' radio button is enabled
And 'Synovialitis' radio button is enabled
And 'Rupture' radio button is enabled
And 'Insertion anterior joint capsule' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Adhesive Capsulitis' radio button
Then 'Thickening of the joint capsule in the axillary recessus > 3 mm' checkbox is enabled
And 'Thickening of the coracohumeral ligament > 3 mm' checkbox is enabled
And 'Pericapsular edema' checkbox is enabled
And 'Edema around rotator interval and biceps anchor' checkbox is enabled
And 'Increased CA-enhancement by rotator interval & biceps anchor' checkbox is enabled
And 'Increased CA-enhancement of the capsule & pericapsular' checkbox is enabled
And 'Obliteration of the triangular fat body between coracoid/ joint capsule/ coracohumeral ligament' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Synovialitis' radio button
Then 'Proliferations' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Insertion anterior joint capsule' checkbox
Then 'Type 1: In or directly at the labrum' radio button is enabled
And 'Type 2: max. 10 mm beside to the labrum' radio button is enabled
And 'Type 3: > 10 mm beside to the labrum' radio button is enabled
